		<title>Aurascape Raises $50M to Secure Enterprise AI Applications</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/aurascape-raises-50m-to-secure-enterprise-ai-applications/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 20:10:54 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=199805</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Aurascape has secured $50 million in funding to grow its AI platform and assist organizations in grappling with the increasing challenges posed by generative AI tools. The round was led</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/aurascape-raises-50m-to-secure-enterprise-ai-applications/" data-wpel-link="internal">Aurascape Raises $50M to Secure Enterprise AI Applications</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://aurascape.ai/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Aurascape </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has secured $50 million in </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/milltech-bags-60m-to-scale-treasury-and-fx-tools/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">to grow its AI platform and assist organizations in grappling with the increasing challenges posed by generative AI tools. The round was led by Menlo Ventures and Mayfield Fund and also included Celesta Capital and venture investors in broad technology, leading the company to emerge from stealth.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cybersecurity veterans from top security companies, including Zscaler, Palo Alto Networks, and Netskope, established Aurascape. Its leadership explains that currently available web security solutions have not been architected to allow for the complex data flows that existing AI implementations require. Many AI systems have multiple signalling protocols and dynamic data exchanges that traditional security tools are generally unable to monitor or control. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Existing security infrastructure built for general traffic will not be effective for protecting AI traffic. Aurascape wishes to build its security infrastructure for AI traffic for better visibility and the security of enterprises.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Rising Security Concerns Around AI Adoption</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Organisations have significantly increased their use of AI since the introduction of generative AI tools like ChatGPT. Firms leverage AI for numerous activities, including content creation, software engineering and operational streamlining. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">But it has also posed issues for security. Workers are exploring and testing third-party AI applications without approvals from IT teams, so the phenomenon is what industry experts now refer to as &#8220;shadow AI&#8221;.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_199806" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199806" class="size-large wp-image-199806" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/AI-1-1024x576.jpg" alt="AI" width="1024" height="576" /><p id="caption-attachment-199806" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Organisations are using unapproved AI tools, like Shadow AI, which could potentially leak critical company data. This includes storing and processing the data shared on the platform and possibly using it to train machine learning models. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">Aurascape hopes to address this issue by providing enterprise customers with visibility and security for interactions on their network against a web of things.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/milltech-bags-60m-to-scale-treasury-and-fx-tools/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">MillTech Bags $60M to Scale Treasury and FX Tools</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Aurascape’s AI-Native Security Platform</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Aurascape is building an AI-native security platform for an AI-native era. Instead of using typical cybersecurity solutions like firewalls and proxies, the company had to develop an AI-native security system that could evaluate how workers were actually working with AI tools.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform monitors AI traffic and usage trends for thousands of apps. It can identify openings for data leaks or other malicious activity by following prompts, output, or any additional communication.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Aurascape analyses a wide range of content types: text, images, sound, video, and source code. Security teams can track AI activity, independent of the type of information employees are sharing over AI services.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A further important aspect of the platform is automated policy enforcement. Using it, firms can set policies limiting the access that their AI applications have to corporate data to prevent it from leaking to outside models.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Growing Market for AI Security</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Aurascape&#8217;s launch date coincides with a rush among cybersecurity companies to close off the opportunities for exploits posed by generative AI. Businesses feel forced to innovate and secure at the same time. AI has the potential to dramatically boost productivity but also provide cybercriminals with new avenues of attack and accidentally expose data.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Security platforms, such as Aurascape, seek to close this gap by making it easier for enterprises to adopt AI-powered solutions while still providing governance, control, and compliance. Ahead of the close of its recent Series A financing of $50 million, Aurascape will use the proceeds to speed up the development of its platform, grow its engineering team and deploy the platform to more enterprise customers.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/aurascape-raises-50m-to-secure-enterprise-ai-applications/" data-wpel-link="internal">Aurascape Raises $50M to Secure Enterprise AI Applications</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
