					<description><![CDATA[<p>Chapter, the hottest rising star of the &#8220;AgeTech&#8221; industry, has today announced the closing of a $100 million Series E funding round. The influx of funds has been a significant</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/chapter-secures-100m-to-bridge-seniors-and-ai-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal">Chapter Secures $100M to Bridge Seniors and AI Tech</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://askchapter.org/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Chapter</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, the hottest rising star of the &#8220;AgeTech&#8221; industry, has today announced the closing of a $100 million Series E </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/milltech-bags-60m-to-scale-treasury-and-fx-tools/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. The influx of funds has been a significant achievement for the New York-based startup that now claims to be the de facto &#8220;trust layer&#8221; between ageing Americans and encumbered modern medicine and finance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Most notably, Generation Investment Management led the round with substantial investments from Fifth Down Capital and 8VC. Other already heavy investors, including Stripes, Addition, and Susa Ventures, also doubled down, showing a lot of faith in Chapter&#8217;s goal to reinvent retirement with AI.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Bridging the &#8220;Digital Gray&#8221; Gap</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The tech industry has failed to cater to the 55-plus. For over 20 years, seniors had been forced to deal with cobweb-filled systems to access their Medicare and social security, yet the social media boom has been targeted at most other demographics. Not anymore, however, as Chapter founder and CEO Cobi Blumenfeld Gantz has a different venture in mind.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Most technology companies ignore retirees,&#8221; said Blumenfeld Gantz in the announcement. &#8220;Our goal is to make sure that every senior is able to protect their health, wealth and identity by making the products we wish we had for our own parents when entering retirement.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_199786" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199786" class="size-full wp-image-199786" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/CHAPTER_LOGO_BLACK.jpg" alt="Chapter Logo" width="480" height="117" /><p id="caption-attachment-199786" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Chapter</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chapter&#8217;s most significant offering is an AI-native Medicare navigation platform. Whereas brokers may simply provide search results for 10–15% of available plans, Chapter&#8217;s proprietary algorithms analyze all 24,000+ plans nationwide and identify the best fit for the customer&#8217;s health needs and budget.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/milltech-bags-60m-to-scale-treasury-and-fx-tools/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">MillTech Bags $60M to Scale Treasury and FX Tools</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">How AI is Revolutionizing Senior Care</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new investment arrives at a moment in which the era of &#8220;agentic AI&#8221; (artificial intelligence capable of undertaking complex tasks on its own accord) is emerging and transforming the professional services industry. Chapter leverages these innovations to offer an unprecedented level of &#8220;white-glove&#8221; service to the average investor.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By leveraging its AI platform, the company can:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Spot benefits not considered</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Discover secondary coverage or inexpensive prescriptions that human agents tend to overlook.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Unbiased Advocacy:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Because the platform is data-driven, the &#8220;commission bias&#8221; in the insurance industry no longer exists.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Proactive Planning</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Forecasting future healthcare costs, which can be based on present health trends, and assisting seniors to modify their saving strategy accordingly.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Expanding Beyond Medicare</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Where the first Chapter focused on Medicare, the 100 million Series E will help build Chapter into a comprehensive retirement operating system. Upcoming plans include releasing other services such as life insurance, estate planning and senior-specific savings accounts.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Generation Investment Management&#8217;s partner Anthony Woolf pointed out that trust was Chapter&#8217;s key asset. &#8220;As our life world is reconfigured by artificial intelligence, Chapter is foresighted to help drive technologies forward for seniors&#8217; benefit,&#8221; Woolf stated.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In the last year, the company has more than doubled its valuation, mirroring demand for &#8220;Silver Economy&#8221; technology. In the context of 10,000 baby boomers a day, Chapter&#8217;s AI-powered bridge looks set to be the most important infrastructure in American retirement.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/chapter-secures-100m-to-bridge-seniors-and-ai-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal">Chapter Secures $100M to Bridge Seniors and AI Tech</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
